      viaMatter is OMITTED entirely (not null) when source-record has no matter linkage; memberships[] is one-entry-per-role projected from upstream LookupUserMembership node's byRole bucket.
      Justification (§11): existing = BuildNotificationEntity itself (lines 471-546); extension = YES (in-method extension, no new types/DI/endpoints); cost-of-doing-nothing = FR-13 + FR-14 fail (EntityNameValidator allow-list cannot be built, widget narration loses grounding).
      Tests: 5 new FR-6 tests pass (AC-6a enriched-fields, omission rule, multi-role, AC-6b backward-compat, AC-6c &lt;2KB / &lt;10KB).
      Build clean. Publish-size 46.31 MB (+1.33 MB vs PR 1 baseline 44.98 MB; not from this task — accumulated PR 2 changes). CVE: 1 pre-existing HIGH (Microsoft.Kiota.Abstractions GHSA-7j59-v9qr-6fq9) carried from master — NOT introduced by task 020.
      TTL fix at line 490 (ttlinseconds = 604800) preserved untouched. Idempotency check (CheckForDuplicateNotificationAsync) preserved.
